{"build_type":"library","description":"Rollback-aware boot kernel entry (Channel B, additive -- does not touch the proven kernel-roots). Same bring-up as the gate-aware kernel-root (install fixed arena, read boot config, record identity, install the portal, launch init), then performs a host-side HTTP health check by itself via raw socket syscalls: it calls the kernel HTTP health client against the configured port (health_port_hi, health_port_lo) sending health_request, and records the 1/0 healthy result as a single decimal character into the health_out path from the config. Finally it runs the unified serve-and-shutdown poll loop (park). This first build records the health verdict so the synergy (kernel HTTP client reaching the in-boot HTTP edge) can be confirmed; mark-good of the boot counter and crash tracking are layered on next. All paths and port bytes come from the boot config (no hardcoded literals).","module_name":"enter-portal-kernel-arena-verifying-health-recording-generation","package_name":"enter-portal-kernel-arena-verifying-health-recording-generation","function_definitions":{"enter-portal-kernel-arena-verifying-health-recording-generation":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"env","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"config_path","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"four","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":4},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"c40","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":40},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"c48","variable_type":"i64","as